From 670ed68a2cd9655632f4795d1fba724e948aa46a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 14:50:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/7] Fix 4 AI Employees permanently stuck on WAIT due to dead
 event subscriptions

Audited every employee that reacts to event-bus data (30 total) by cross-
referencing every employees/*.py event_bus.subscribe() call against every
event_type actually published anywhere in the codebase. Found 4 employees
subscribed to event names that no producer ever publishes, so their
`latest_results` cache was permanently empty and they only ever reported
their hardcoded default_decision:

- RiskEmployee (EMP-RSK): subscribed to "safety_status", which does not
  exist as an event (it's only a dict key returned by SafetyEngine's
  pull-style get_dashboard_metrics()). SafetyEngine.check_order() ->
  SafetyManager.evaluate_order() actually emits "safety_blocked" /
  "safety_check_passed" per order. Rewired to those two events.
- MarketRegimeEmployee (EMP-RGM): subscribed to "regime_changed", which
  nothing publishes; RegimeEngine actually publishes "market_regime". Also
  fixed the handler, which read payload["regime"] instead of the real key
  payload["market_regime"].
- CapitalProtectionEmployee (EMP-CPT): subscribed to "pnl_update"; the real
  event PortfolioEngine publishes is "pnl_updated" (trailing d).
- PaperTradingEmployee (EMP-PPR): subscribed to "paper_status_changed",
  which nothing publishes; PaperTradingEngine publishes "paper_trade_started"
  / "paper_trade_stopped" instead. Rewired to react to both.

Verified live against the running server: MarketRegimeEmployee and
CapitalProtectionEmployee immediately began reporting real decisions
(RANGE_BOUND/55%, BUY/85%) instead of their static defaults. RiskEmployee
and PaperTradingEmployee are now correctly wired but, by design, only ever
had something to report once an order is actually attempted or a paper
session is started - their inputs are execution-reactive, not market-data-
driven, so a permanent WAIT before the first order/session event is
expected, not a bug.

Audited the remaining employees too: all "candle"-driven and
"option_chain_updated"-driven employees (Momentum, VWAP, SmartMoney,
Liquidity, OrderFlow, News, EconomicCalendar, EventRisk, OI, PCR, Greeks,
MaxPain, the specialist desks, VolumeIntelligence, TrendIntelligence,
OptionFlowIntelligence) already subscribe to real, live-firing producers.
Their current WAIT/NEUTRAL/NO TRADE outputs (e.g. TrendIntelligence needs
20 completed candles before it emits anything but NO TRADE) are genuine
warm-up states from receiving live mock-feed data, not wiring bugs.

Added 4 regression tests (test_new_specialists.py) publishing the real
event types and asserting each employee's latest_results updates.

